<topic id='business_definition_reasonable_offer.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Reasonable Offer - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_reasonable_offer">Reasonable Offer</xref>
 is an 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_appointment_offer">APPOINTMENT OFFER</xref>
 or 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_offer_of_admission">OFFER OF ADMISSION</xref>.        </p>
      <p>An offer is reasonable where:</p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <p>
the offer of an 
                          <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_out-patient_appointment">Out-Patient Appointment</xref>
 or an 
                          <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_offer_of_admission">OFFER OF ADMISSION</xref>
 is for a time and date three or more weeks from the time that the offer was made
                          <b>or</b>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>
the 
                          <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 accepts the offer
                          <b>or</b>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>
the offer is for the first 
                          <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_genitourinary_consultant_clinic_attendance">Genitourinary Consultant Clinic Attendance</xref>
 in a 
                          <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_sexual_health_and_hiv_episode">Sexual Health and HIV Episode</xref>
               <b>or</b>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>
the offer is for any 
                          <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_appointment">APPOINTMENT</xref>
 for treatment in a 
                          <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_cancer_treatment_period">Cancer Treatment Period</xref>
               <b>or</b>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>
the offer of an 
                          <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_appointment">APPOINTMENT</xref>
 for a non-outpatient 
                          <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_contact">CARE CONTACT</xref>
 provided by a 
                          <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_community_health_service">Community Health Service</xref>
 complies with local, publicly available/published policies for access to that 
                          <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_service">SERVICE</xref>.  These local policies should be clearly defined and specifically protect the clinical interests of vulnerable 
                          <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 (e.g. children) and must have been agreed with clinicians, commissioners, 
                          <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 and other stakeholders.                </p>
         </li>
      </ul>
  </div>
